.TH "snd_ac97_update_power" 9 "snd_ac97_update_power" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_ac97_update_power \- update the powerdown register
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_ac97_update_power
.BI "(struct snd_ac97 *ac97 "  ","
.BI "int reg "  ","
.BI "int powerup "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ac97" 12
the codec instance
.IP "reg" 12
the rate register, e.g. AC97_PCM_FRONT_DAC_RATE
.IP "powerup" 12
non-zero when power up the part
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Update the AC97 powerdown register bits of the given part.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero.
